# AEGIS eBPF Agent - Backend Integration Guide

## Overview

This guide demonstrates how the backend communicates with the AEGIS eBPF agent to enforce network policies in real-time using kernel-space eBPF programs and BPF maps.

## Architecture

```
Backend System → HTTP API → AEGIS Agent → eBPF Maps → Kernel Enforcement
                    ↓
                Telemetry ← Agent Stats ← eBPF Statistics
```

## 1. Backend to Agent Communication

### Agent API Endpoints

- **Policy Management**: `http://agent-host:7070/policies`
- **Status Check**: `http://agent-host:7070/status`
- **Statistics**: `http://agent-host:7070/stats`
- **Health Check**: `http://agent-host:7070/health`

### Authentication
```http
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <token>  # If authentication enabled
```

